content: Definitely a hidden gem of a game. I've been hooked for a few days now. I enjoy the systems in place for skills and receiving/leveling guns. The pet system is also fun and interesting. I've had no issue with controls, and find them rather smooth so far. The only issue I have is that the auto-fire system was changed slightly. My player will now immediately shoot at enemies that enter firing range, even if I'm not aiming at them. I liked the old auto-fire system that required you to target an enemy first. This is just personal preference though. Great work so far, Dev!
One few I actually play nice updates thanks !

content: Great game. Progress feels fun and rewarding. There is no clear story after you beat floor 10 but it seems the developer plans to make much more available which really adds to the excitement. I'm at floor 13 and have got all donation pets and blood gem pets. Ghost cemetary is very fun and the pet skills really add a good element of chance and variety. I am using the pets +15% pet+character movespeed for chararacter and +24.7% character movespeed on my gun. This is a great tactic for the ghost cemetary for death cave. I feel the rewards are fair and I'm enjoying the game. I know there is much more progress for me while I strengthen my character and it's very rewarding. I can note that currently there is an issue with auto aiming, where if you haven't a finger down on the right side of screen before you start moving, that you may start to aim towards the direction you move. Annoying for some but the game really hasn't any bugs if you avoid it with that in mind.
replyContent: As a developer, I feel honored and lucky to have a player like you. Thank you for enjoying the game so much and leaving behind the experience. I believe the game will get better and better. I hope you will find more fun in the game，good lucky my friend.
